	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Aug 17th 4:46 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.08]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>As a cleric that begins at level one, you get the impression that you can nuke, melee, tank, and heal and buff well.&nbsp;&nbsp;This is true until you can meditate.  I suggest that young clerics learn early that their healing is the number one priority of the class. If you want to nuke or melee, be a ranger, druid, or paladin.  While you have the ability to nuke and melee, after level 8 its not worth the lost time meditating for heals.  <br><br>The key to being a successful cleric is keeping the party alive, and you are equipped well to do that.  Clerics are specialists, and should never forget that because its a great advantage in tough areas.  <br><br>My wisdom is summed up by this:  understand your role, take advantage of your strengths by fighting challenging things, and never try to do more than a cleric is able to do, even at high levels you will be entrusted with the health of your group.<br>&nbsp;<br>Alvolcar Kneebyter<br>Cleric of the Solistari<br>www.solistari.com<br>Karana</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
