	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Aug 21st 4:58 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>A spell many clerics don't use is Atone.&nbsp;&nbsp;Atone works the same way as the Enchanter spell Mem Blur.  It completely wipes a mob hate list.  If you are grouped with an Enchanter (who may not have time to cast mem blur) it will effectively stop the mob from agroing the Enchanter and get it back on the tanks.<br><br>I have met many clerics who don't even know what Atone does.  They assume it is another spell in the lull/soothe line and of limited usefulness.  It is in fact a lifesaver whenever a mob frenzys on a character other than the biggest tank.  I will agree, however, that Enchanters and to a lesser extent Wizards need all of the armor and hit point buffs available to survive.<br><br>Baguette Ovenfresh<br>Cleric of the 45th Season<br>Quellious<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
